- Man: I need cover!</i>

33:34.597 --> 33:36.431
Just keep it still.

33:36.466 --> 33:39.935
<i>Damn this. Goddamn bugs.</i>

34:10.828 --> 34:12.260
<i>Follow this barbed wire</i>

34:12.295 --> 34:14.229
<i>And find out where the bridge is.</i>

34:20.401 --> 34:22.403
Is he okay?

34:22.437 --> 34:24.938
Yeah, he's okay.

34:24.972 --> 34:27.070
He's sleeping.

34:28.970 --> 34:32.069
- Manny all right?
- Haven't seen him.

34:35.770 --> 34:38.102
Guess I need a new one, huh?

34:39.071 --> 34:40.669
You and me both.

34:51.973 --> 34:54.574
- Has he had any morphine?
- No.

34:54.609 --> 34:56.943
thanks.

34:58.144 --> 35:01.246
Hold him down.

35:06.447 --> 35:08.614
Hey, sergeant, hand me that pail.

35:14.483 --> 35:16.483
<i>Those are third-degree burns.</i>

35:16.518 --> 35:18.985
Have a seat over there and
we'll get to you when we can.

35:24.689 --> 35:27.455
Sir, anybody bring in
sergeant rodriguez last night?

35:27.489 --> 35:30.921
- Manny rodriguez?
- I wish I could keep track.

35:52.986 --> 35:55.086
Check the aid station?

36:03.792 --> 36:07.389
<i>Doesn't take long to get
ripe in this heat.</i>

36:07.424 --> 36:09.023
<i>Man #2: They're real damn stupid</i>

36:09.057 --> 36:10.957
<i>To keep running into a
machine gun like that.</i>

36:10.992 --> 36:14.392
<i>- Man #3: Morning, sir.
- Puller: As you were.</i>

36:20.328 --> 36:22.095
Nice work.

36:26.399 --> 36:29.901
I'm putting you in
for a medal, john.

36:29.935 --> 36:33.701
We're gonna be moving west
toward lunga, up on the ridge.

36:33.736 --> 36:35.835
164th's gonna take this position.

36:37.936 --> 36:41.069
- Get yourselves some hot chow.
- Aye aye, sir.

36:42.871 --> 36:47.973
Captain.

38:57.591 --> 38:59.692
It's gone, isn't it?

39:08.071 --> 39:10.473
Doesn't matter.

39:11.742 --> 39:14.544
I'm enlisting tomorrow.

39:14.578 --> 39:16.213
I'd do it tonight
if they were open.

39:16.247 --> 39:19.449
Eugene-- - I don't need
your permission, father.

39:22.320 --> 39:24.588
I haven't for some time.

39:39.217 --> 39:42.922
The worst thing about treating those
combat boys from the great war

39:42.956 --> 39:47.095
Wasn't that they had
had their flesh torn.

39:48.865 --> 39:52.467
It was that they had had
their souls torn out.

39:54.637 --> 39:57.538
<i>I don't want to look in
your eyes someday</i>

39:57.572 --> 40:02.610
<i>And see no spark, no love,
no... No life.</i>

40:03.846 --> 40:06.584
That would break my heart.

40:21.007 --> 40:23.942
Give me some time to break
the news to your mother.

40:25.546 --> 40:29.015
After supper I'll take
deacon for a walk.

40:29.050 --> 40:31.152
That would do it.

40:39.834 --> 40:42.036
Thank you, father.

40:45.908 --> 40:48.010
Come on, deacon.

40:59.723 --> 41:02.323
